t concern narrowly defined family history, but is an attempt to examine fraternal relations in the early Middle Ages as a multidimensional cultural phenomenon. As the author seeks to demonstrate, it is difficult to speak of kinship in the ninth century and later without being aware of the religious and ideological implications of the transformations taking place at the time, even if direct traces of the impact of moralizing and theological teachings on the conduct of individuals are hard to capture in the sources.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aKinshipzEuropexHistoryyTo 1500. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  abrotherhood.  abrothers.  aearly Middle Ages.  akinship.1 aKijak, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781802701234?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781802701234zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781802701234/original  a978-3-11-102374-8 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131913-1 EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2